    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-12-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-12-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="1790"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1790">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 033.1100 K77/219b.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-12-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 8, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received from His Excellency, Señor Don
                    Manuel E. Araujo, President of El Salvador, a handsome volume entitled: “Album
                    del Centenario” in memory of the one hundredth anniversary of the beginning of
                    the war of independence of El Salvador and the other Republics of Central
                        America.<note n="1" xml:id="d1790fn1">The “Pink Book of Salvador,”
                        containing an account of the Secretary’s visit (File No. 716.000).</note>
                </p>
                <p>You will avail yourself of an early opportunity to express in person to His
                    Excellency, President Araujo, my thanks for this valuable work, so interesting
                    and instructive, which has served to recall to me with pleasure my recent visit
                    to El Salvador and the other republics of Central America.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.],</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
